  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Child begs admission to the Brook Farm community for Caroline (Henshaw) Colt, the widow of John C. Colt, and her child. Describes her as an &quot;ignorant, worthy, affectionate German girl,&quot; and outlines the circumstances of her marriage to Colt.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">See George Willis Cooke&apos;s book, John Sullivan Dwight : brook-farmer, editor, and critic of music : a biography; (1898). On page 76, there is a reference to Mrs. Colt in a letter from Dwight to Mrs. Child, Dec. 25, 1843.</subfield>
